20 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Preemption. This chapter abrogates the common law of public nuisance
21 and private nuisance in this state and supersedes any other state statute to the extent there is a conflict.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Liability for a public nuisance. (1) A person may be liable under a
24 public nuisance cause of action only if that person proximately caused the public nuisance at the time the public
25 nuisance was created, which includes controlling the unlawful activity that proximately caused the public
26 nuisance. Public nuisance is not a strict liability offense.
